    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden text-content text-secondary"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p class="p1">Profiling your site is extremely useful not only for debugging and performance testing but also for learning about how your site handles requests.</p>
<p class="p1">Symfony 2 comes with a bundle (like a Drupal module but for Symfony) called WebProfiler Bundle which collects information about each request made to your application and allows you to visualize it in the browser.</p>
<p class="p1">Drupal 8 doesn’t include the Web Profiler bundle in core. However, there already is a <a href="https://drupal.org/project/webprofiler">contrib module</a> for it. Make sure to install any dependencies before enabling the module.</p>
<p class="p1">The module will render a fixed bar at the bottom of each page for users with the <em>View webprofiler toolbar</em> permission. The bar provides a summary of the collected data from the profiler.</p>
